caption: The Kroft is located inside the Anaheim Packing District. They are popular for good reason - their food is delicious! I’ve ordered their Braised Beef Poutine and, although much different from my first poutine in Eastern Canada, I enjoyed the modern American take of this classic French-Canadian recipe!

When I arrived at the building I didn't know where this place even was but searching I did end up finding this place. It wasn't expensive and the food came out pretty fast for how busy it was. The food was awesome and better than I expected. I will definitely come back to try something else on the menu!
Great food great service

Local counter-serve spot with creative poutines and sandwiches. They’re still operating during covid for takeout and delivery. Came here on a Sunday around noon and there wasn’t a line. You order at the counter and they’ll take your phone …
The sandwich and fries are all good. It was  a quick visit though, service is nice.
Good prices for a lot of food.  Food is very heavy and you will need a nap afterwards!
Food was great! Person giving out orders seemed short staffed and needed more help. It took a while for us to get our completed order.
The loco moco poutine is one of best things ive ever tasted in my life .

My goodness, the poutines here are delicious, it's such an unique blend of flavors and The Kroft definitely does it right. I've been to Canada to go visit Quebec before and this is on par with the poutine restaurants found there where the …

3.5  I've seen this place here and there on Instagram and it piqued my interest because fries! While browsing through their menu, I was having a hard time trying to decide because everything sounded so good. I was leaning towards the …
Must have poutine!
Great service.  Not crazy about the coleslaw or regular poutine.   The sandwiches and fries are nice.
(Translated by Google) Fireee  (Original) Fireee

Phenomenal food served in larger portions. Well worth the price. I certainly wish that I was in town more frequently so I could try the rest of the menu. While the braised beef was amazing, the tremendous fries made me very curious about their varieties of poutine. Definitely check it out if you're around the Packing District!

Have been craving a French dip sandwich and was happy to see one on the menu here. Sadly, for being one of the more expensive sandwiches on the menu, it was extremely disappointing. The bread choice is all wrong for one. It’s a very sweet, …
Yes. Go now
Came here for the poutine. Tasted great but disappointed about the unmelted cheese curds (they had one job!)
The Kroft is a nice fusion spot with a pretty diverse menu & a nice variety of eats.

The braised pork poutine is hands down my favorite out of the three poutines I've tried here (chicken pot pie and the loco moco). The loco moco is a close second. There's a yolky egg on top along with a meatloaf and the ketchup sauce makes it pretty sweet. I love eating my poutine with the Louisiana hot sauce to give it an extra kick.
The food was amazing!  They have so many options, and they offer military discount!  I can't wait to go back and try something else.
Quick and friendly service with delicious food. The fried chicken poutine was great with the country gravy.
Great Poutine!
It's alright. The portions are kinda small
Only spot I get legit poutine at

This is one of the many bright spots of the Anaheim Packing District. It was a little bit of a challenge to actually decide on one thing from the menu, since they ALL sounded delicious!The fries were perfectly crispy so they didn't get …

What's Good: the Porchetta sandwich is good - good mix of meat, fatty pieces and crunchy pieces. Could go well with one of the dipping sauces (25 cents each). The Loco Moco Poutine is tasty but very filling - definitely a sharable. After a …

Poutine on another level. Loco moco poutine we ordered because of the picture they put up while we were walking by. It was as incredible as it looked. Meatloaf, gravy, scallions, fried onions, fried egg, and more. It was bomb.

Excellent porchetta sando for $10.  The pork dip sandwhich is not so great however; meat is mushy and wet even before dipping, making for a horrible texture and mouth feel.  Stick with their tried and true porchetta.  I have had their …

If you are familiar with their poutines they are delicious but I can say they have changed their meat source and it's not as good as before.  When I crave pickled red onions the short rib poutine is what I order. Another favorite is the …
What can I say? The food was amazing? The employees were kind and helpful? Both true. Just go there and order the chicken fried poutine.
If you like poutine, check out the Kroft!
The food was amazing, for the price, the only downside would be the parking is limited but besides that really good place to get something to eat.
Absolutely loved it! Definitely need to come back and you need to go!
Must go to spot in Packing House

The sandwiches are excellent! Flavorful, fresh, and always delicious! The poutine is good, but leaves a little to be desired... Sadly, The gravy is on the bland side.  Finished it off with an order of cheese curds which redeemed the meal! They are BOMB!!

Came to Anaheim Packing District to try out different food at a time, The Kroft caught my attention with its mouthwatering with its Classic Poutine, with fries, meat, and egg.  The food is packaged in a paper box which is very convenient …

Nice sandwich place in the Packing House. It is one of the places that opens later and the food is made to order. I had the Cubano and enjoyed it even though I don't like pulled pork. I would love to come back and try their other menu items next time.
Sides are good.
Amazing food

Found this great place in a cool food court very close to disneyland.  Had the chicken katsu curry poutine and it definitely hit the spot. Great flavor, fries weren't overly soggy from the curry, katsu was fried right, and delicious cheese curds. If you're in or around this area and haven't been here. Go check it out.

Location - At the Anaheim Packing District  Parking - Lots of street parking around but still hard to find a spot open. Recommend paying $3 for valet.  Venue - Located on the first floor towards the back. Very small just like any other …
I'm from Quebec and let me tell you this is the best poutine out here in California. Taste amazing, the people are nice (The Canadian spirit you know), and did I say it's amazing? TRY IT!!!
I am French Canadian. I know poutine. This is not only poutine. This is some really good poutine.

I can see why this place has high ratings. Their porchetta sandwich is really good - filled with a decent amount of juicy roasted pork and slathered with this cilantro pesto type of sauce (little spicy kick to it). Worth trying!  Seating on …

If you're looking for a something light to snack on with friends, this is a great place. Especially with a place like the Anaheim Packing District, you'll want to save room for dessert, drinks, and more!  About the place: located inside the …

Poutine, OC style. The #1 comfort food perfectly executed. Including the Brussel Sprouts, one of the best deals in the Packing District. Service was friendly, one of the locations that stay open later.
Great place with good food, there is always a line but service is overall fast. wish there were more room to eat
You gotta get the Porchetta and cheese curds!
This place is ridiculously good!
Wow! Best experience with Erwin! He was quick, attentive, and incredibly helpful. The atmosphere and food were both amazing!!! We highly recommend coming here.

Unable to review, so will receive one star for a bad experience and not being prepared at opening and told us we had to wait 30-45 minutes for a popular menu item. Hopefully they can step their game up and be prepared like a professional restaurant.
Gotta try the pumpkin bread pudding topped with ice cream! The cranberry turkey sandwich is a perfect combination.  Fresh and flavorful
Great food. My favorite is the Loco Moco.

This place is the Valhalla of comfort food.  There are multiple variations on Canada's beloved poutine.  The portions are very generous and very easy to share with a large party.  All of my orders came out picture perfect and tasted even better than they looked!  Will definitely be back for more.
Loved that I can get moco loco and a side order of fried cheese curds! Friendly staff too!
Hearty soul food
Tried the short rib melt sandwich with the garlic fries, all I can say is wow. Staff is super friendly and helpful, will be back for sure.
Cheese Curds + Beer = PERFECT!
Amazing!!!! That's it. You can't come to Anaheim and not try this place.
The Porchetta sandwich was disappointing.  The Country Fried Chicken Poutine was delicious, but too rich for just the two of us to split.
They have great poutine and their sandwiches are decent.

Poutine is now my favorite food. I have been wanting to try this place for so long! Finally made it here. Tried the classic poutine and the chicken pot fries this time. Perfectly cooked fries. Delicious gravy. Cheese curds were better than …
The Poutine's sauce is what led the food bears its name, however taste wise could still be improved with greater mix and spices to complement and bring about the popularity of this canadian food

Poutine had great gravy, but needed more of it. Pickled onions were unexpected, french fries were excellent. Was really excited about the brussels sprouts, but then they added balsamic, which I did not realize would be on them and was not a welcome addition.
Short rib poutine-deliciously tender w cheese curds, gravy, onion. Fried cheese curds-looks like tater tots. Pretty good. Ribeye dip-bread and meat were all very tender.

Tried the short rib poutine. Nothing to get too excited about. Jalapeño slaw had a really nice kick to it. Make sure you’re okay with serious spicy if you order this. Wanted to order the chili mac but they were out. Maybe next time.

I've been meaning to try The Kroft for a minute now.  However, my intention was to try the one at the District in Tustin but somehow the stars aligned and I came here instead to try the one in the Packing District.  The line wasn't too bad …
Really good poutine.
the chicken pot fries with extra mushrooms. just get this. other than that, the sandwiches are all really good as well. seating can be a problem, as is parking. try to come on a weekday

The Kroft restaurant is hidden inside the Anaheim Packing House serving up comfort food such as scrumptious sandwiches and mouth watering fries. I’ve been wanting to try this place out.  There was a line to order, but glad there was one as …

The poutine is so good. $8 for most of the poutine selection, $1 more for mushrooms... Well worth the investment. The portion size is generous. The line gets pretty long here, especially dinner time. i'd rank the chicken pot fries, loco moco, and short rib as my 3 favorite poutines
